    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <bold>IADLXDisplaySettingsChangedListener</bold> interface is implemented in the application to receive an event from ADLX when display settings change.</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>An instance of the implemented <bold>IADLXDisplaySettingsChangedListener</bold> interface must be passed to <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_display_changed_handling__add_display_settings_event_listener" kindref="compound">AddDisplaySettingsEventListener</ref> to register for notifications when display settings change.<linebreak/>
 For more information about subscribing for notifications, refer to <ref refid="page_guide_event" kindref="compound">Subscribing to Event Notifications using ADLX</ref>.<linebreak/>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Methods </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_display_settings_changed_listener__on_display_settings_changed" kindref="compound">OnDisplaySettingsChanged</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>The <bold>OnDisplaySettingsChanged</bold> method is called by ADLX when the display settings change.   </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Requirements </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Header</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>include &quot;IDisplays.h&quot;</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Minimum version</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>1.0</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Example </heading>
</para>
<para>To see how to use this interface in a C++ application, refer to the <ref refid="cpp__sync_display_receive" kindref="compound">SyncDisplayReceive C++ sample</ref>.<linebreak/>
 For a C application, refer to the <ref refid="c__sync_display_receive" kindref="compound">SyncDisplayReceive C sample</ref>.</para>
